Lagos – Activities on the floor of The Nigerian Stock Exchange ended the week on a positive note as both the All-Share Index (ASI) and Market Capitalisation appreciated by 0.08 per cent week-on-week to settle at 41, 504.51points and N14.993 trillion  respectively. The market had experienced three days of closing negative during the week, while investors gained N18.00 billion in value. In all, a total turnover of 1.541 billion shares worth N16.647 billion in 18, 805 deals were traded last week by investors compared to a total of 2, 328 billion shares valued at N28.927 billion that exchanged hands in the previous week in 25,530 deals. All sectoral indices and group stock trackers finished lower during the week with the exception of the NSE’s Premium index, which rose by 1.15 per cent, NSE’s Consumer Goods index, rising by 1.73 per cent, NSE’s Lotus II which grew by 1.58 per cent and NSE’s Pension Index which increased by 0.34 per cent, among others. Consequently, the financial services sector (measured by volume) led the activity chart with 1.024 billion shares valued at N10.946 billion traded in 11, 019 deals; contributing 66.44 per cent and 65.75 per cent to the total equity turnover volume and value respectively. The Consumer Goods industry followed with 213.704 million shares worth N3.053 billion in 2, 693 deals, while the turnover of the Oil and Gas Industry stood at 158.643 million shares valued at N908.260 million in 1, 897 deals. Specifically, trading in the top three equities namely: Zenith International Bank, Champion Breweries and Skye Bank ,accounted for 485.832 million shares worth N5.851 billion in 2, 221 deals, thus contributing 31.53 per cent and 35.15 per cent to the total equity turnover volume and value in that order. Also, 40 equities appreciated in price during the week, higher than 33 of the previous week, while 40 equities depreciated in price, lower than 49 equities of the previous week and 91 equities remained unchanged higher than 89 equities recorded in the earlier week. An additional volume of 836, 983, 125 ordinary shares of  Morison Industries Plc, resulting from rights issue were added to its outstanding shares on Monday March 26, 2018. By this, the total outstanding shares of the company has now increased to 989, 161,875 ordinary shares In the same vein, the price of Guaranty Trust Bank was adjusted on March 28, 2018, for a dividend of N2.40 as declared by the board of directors. The last close price was N46.00, hence the ex-dividend price N43.60 Stanbic IBTC Holdings Plc’s price was also adjusted on March 29, 2018, for a dividend of N0.50 as declared by the board of directors. The last closing price was N48.00, hence the ex-dividend price of N47.50 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.